# Dart Standards

## Style
- Line length: 80 chars or fewer
- `PascalCase` classes, `camelCase` members/variables/functions, `snake_case` files
- Arrow syntax for simple one-line functions
- Avoid abbreviations; use meaningful names

## Null Safety & Async
- Soundly null-safe; avoid `!` unless guaranteed non-null
- Use `async`/`await` with robust error handling
- Use `Future` for single async ops, `Stream` for sequences

## Code Quality
- Functions: single purpose, under 20 lines
- Use pattern matching and exhaustive `switch` where they simplify code
- Use records for multiple return values when a class is overkill
- Custom exceptions for domain-specific errors
- Use `dart:developer` log, not print

## Effective Dart
Follow https://dart.dev/effective-dart. Add `///` doc comments to public APIs.
